lenders.name: ALI
lenders.loan_because:
I’m Ali Ouazza , 26 years old. I was born and raised in Zagora ,south east of Morocco, I have five siblings, my mother is house wife , my father died when I was six years old, he was a soldier, and his retirement pension, which represents an amount less than 125$ per month,  is our unique source of funding .
   After my high school, I left Zagora to continue my studies in the university of Marrakech, I did Applied Mathematics, I had my diploma and because I was one of the good student they allowed me to do engineering, I chose finance because I was always passionate about it ,during this period I was always working in my free time tutoring high school students in Math, physics and linguistics in order to cover my education fees.
    This year I’m going to have my engineering diploma, I’m not going to stop there for several reasons; the most important is that studying abroad and having new experience interacting with people of different cultures and knowledge is and will always be my ultimate dream. The second reason is that by having this experience will for sure increase my chance to get the good job that will allow me to help my family financially. I asked the local banks for the possibility to have a loan but I didn’t get a positive answer because I don’t have anyone who has a good and permanent salary to guarantee my repayment and also they don’t lend money for people willing to leave the country. This is why I need this loan, a part of which will cover the procedures of obtaining VISA, and the other will help me with the tuitions, the rent, and other fees related to my studies.
